    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_æppæt" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>æppæt</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ænkæt</orth><form type="variant"
                            ><orth>ænkkæt</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>все</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>everybody</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>всё</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>everything</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>neppætdær</orth></form>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>nenkætdær</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>мы все</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>all of us</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>weppætdær</orth></form>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>wenkætdær</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вы все</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>all of you</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>seppætdær</orth></form>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>senkætdær</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>они все</q>
                        </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (ср. под <ref type="xr"
                                target="#entry_ænxwæcæj"/>: %inenxwæcæjdær%i 'мы все' и пр., а также
                            под <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xædæg"/>: %inæxædæg%i 'мы сами' и
                            пр.)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (compare <ref type="xr"
                                target="#entry_ænxwæcæj"/>: %inenxwæcæjdær%i 'all of us' etc., and
                                also<ref type="xr" target="#entry_xædæg"/>: %inæxædæg%i 'ourselves'
                            etc.)</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>all of them</q>
                        </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (ср. под <ref type="xr"
                                target="#entry_ænxwæcæj"/>: %inenxwæcæjdær%i 'мы все' и пр., а также
                            под <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xædæg"/>: %inæxædæg%i 'мы сами' и
                            пр.)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (compare <ref type="xr"
                                target="#entry_ænxwæcæj"/>: %inenxwæcæjdær%i 'all of us' etc., and
                                also<ref type="xr" target="#entry_xædæg"/>: %inæxædæg%i 'ourselves'
                            etc.)</note></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>atæ ʽppæt</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>все эти</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>all of these</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>ūtæ ʽppæt</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>все те</q>
                            </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (см.<ref type="xr"
                                    target="#entry_ūtæ"/>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                    (see<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ūtæ"/>)</note><note
                                type="comment" xml:lang="ru">; в дигорском %iænkæt%i [см.<ref
                                    type="xr" target="#entry_ænkkæt"/>] вытесняется более
                                употребительным <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ænxwæcæj"/> с тем же
                                значением.</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">; in Digor
                                %iænkæt%i [see<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ænkkæt"/>] is replaced
                                by a more frequent word<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ænxwæcæj"/>
                                with the same meaning.</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>all of those</q>
                            </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (см.<ref type="xr"
                                    target="#entry_ūtæ"/>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                    (see<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ūtæ"/>)</note><note
                                type="comment" xml:lang="ru">; в дигорском %iænkæt%i [см.<ref
                                    type="xr" target="#entry_ænkkæt"/>] вытесняется более
                                употребительным <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ænxwæcæj"/> с тем же
                                значением.</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">; in Digor
                                %iænkæt%i [see<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ænkkæt"/>] is replaced
                                by a more frequent word<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ænxwæcæj"/>
                                with the same meaning.</note></sense>
                    </re>
                </re>
                <re xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                    <lang/>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>ænkkætemi</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>повсюду</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>everywhere</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>æppætæj tyxǵyndær — x˳yssæg</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сильнее всего — сон</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the sleeping is the strongest of all</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            234</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>æppætæj dær fag</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>всего вдоволь</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>there is plenty of everything</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>53</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>aræzt æppætæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>снабжен всем (необходимым)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>supplied by everything (that is needed)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>69</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ne ʽppæt dær būznyg dæ lævaræj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>мы все благодарны за твой подарок</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>we all are grateful for your gift</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>139</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>kæm dyn wydysty ūtʼ æppæt æxca?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>откуда у тебя все эти деньги?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>where did all this money came from?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."
                            /><biblScope>154</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ḱyzǵytæn se ʽppætæj ræsuǧddær wydis Asiat</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>из девушек всех прекрасней была Асиат</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Asiat was the most beautiful of all the girls</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>se ʽnkkætemæj xwæzdær ba sæmæ bæx adtæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>из всех (животных) лучшим был у них конь</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>their horse was the best of all animals</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>314</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Иронская форма %iæppæt%i представляет перебой из *%iæmkæt%i ср.
                    аналогичный перебой в таких словах, как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_typpyr"/>|
                    %ituppur%i ‘бугор’ рядом с <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>tunk’ur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>cæmpul</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><w>cæppul</w>
                        <gloss><q>безрукий</q></gloss></mentioned> рядом с %icænkul%i и др.
                    Восстанавливаемое *%iæmkæt%i(%iæm%i + %ikæt%i) представляет, по-видимому,
                    отражение <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*hama-kaθa</w>
                        <gloss><q>всем домом</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>kata-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>kat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kad</w>
                        <gloss><q>дом</q></gloss></mentioned>. Следы <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>kata-</w></mentioned> усматриваем также в <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kæt"/> ‘конюшня’ (?),<ref type="xr" target="#entry_skʼæt"/>
                    ‘хлев’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kævdæs"/> ‘ясли’ q. v. Семантика
                    отвлеченного понятия ‘весь’, ‘всё’ ведет к конкретным понятиям ‘дом’, ‘село’,
                    ‘общество’ и т. п. Может быть, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>vīśva-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>vispa-</w></mentioned> vispa- образовались от %iviś%i-, %ivis%i- ‘село’,
                    ‘клан’, ‘дом’, как в славянском не случайно совпадение %iвесь%i 'omnis’ и
                    %iвесь%i ‘село’.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Iron form %iæppæt%i represents the alternation from *%iæmkæt%i,
                    compare analogous alternation in such words as<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_typpyr"/>| %ituppur%i ‘hillock’ close to<mentioned
                        xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>tunk’ur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>cæmpul</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><w>cæppul</w>
                        <gloss><q>handless</q></gloss></mentioned>close to %icænkul%i etc.
                    Reconstructed *%iæmkæt%i(%iæm%i + %ikæt)%i represents, apparantely, the
                    reflection of<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*hama-kaθa</w>
                        <gloss><q>(by) everybody in the house</q></gloss></mentioned>; see<mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>kata-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>kat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kad</w>
                        <gloss><q>house</q></gloss></mentioned>. Traces of <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>kata-</w></mentioned> can be also found in<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kæt"/> ‘stable’ (?), <ref type="xr" target="#entry_skʼæt"/>
                    ‘cattle shed’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kævdæs"/> ‘crib’ q. v. The
                    semantics of abstract notion ‘whole’, ‘everything’ leads to specific notions
                    ‘house’, ‘village’, ‘community’ and so on. Probably, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>vīśva-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>vispa-</w></mentioned>derived from %iviś%i-, %ivis%i- ‘village’, ‘clan’,
                    ‘house’, as the combination %ives’%i ‘omnis’ and %ives’%i ‘village’ in Slavic is
                    not accidential.</etym>
            </entry>
